# ResearchFlow — Frontend

> An elegant research workspace that turns complex academic questions into cited, structured reports — powered by an autonomous AI pipeline.

![ResearchFlow](https://img.shields.io/badge/Status-Active-brightgreen) ![Supabase](https://img.shields.io/badge/Auth-Supabase-3ECF8E?logo=supabase) ![FastAPI](https://img.shields.io/badge/Backend-FastAPI-009688?logo=fastapi) ![Vercel](https://img.shields.io/badge/Deploy-Vercel-black?logo=vercel)

---

## 📌 Overview

ResearchFlow is a web-based research assistant that accepts a natural language query and returns a fully synthesised academic report — complete with paper citations, filtered results from Semantic Scholar, arXiv, and PubMed, and a structured markdown report. This repository contains the **frontend only**. The backend (FastAPI + Redis + Groq/Gemini LLMs) is deployed separately on Railway.

---

## ✨ Features

- **Autonomous Research Pipeline** — Submit a query, get back a structured academic report with cited papers
- **Real-time Status UI** — 4-step animated progress tracker while the backend processes your query
- **User Authentication** — Sign up, log in, email verification, and session persistence via Supabase Auth
- **Research History** — Every search is saved per user and accessible from the sidebar; click any item to reload the report instantly
- **Delete History** — Remove individual searches with a hover-revealed × button
- **Markdown Rendering** — Reports rendered with full heading, list, link, and code support via `marked.js`
- **Responsive Auth Modal** — Toggle between Log In and Sign Up with animated transitions, inline error messages, and password visibility toggle
- **Fortune Cookie Widget** — A small interactive break widget for long research sessions
- **Guest Mode** — Full search functionality without an account; history saving requires login

