## 🚀 Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- A [Supabase](https://supabase.com) project
- The ResearchFlow backend running (see backend repo)
- A code editor (VS Code recommended)

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/ResearchFlow_Frontend.git
cd ResearchFlow_Frontend
```

### 2. Set up Supabase credentials

Copy the example auth file and fill in your credentials:

```bash
cp js/auth.example.js js/auth.js
```

Open `js/auth.js` and replace the placeholders:

```js
const SUPABASE_URL  = "https://your-project-id.supabase.co";
const SUPABASE_ANON = "your-publishable-anon-key";

const _supabase = window.supabase.createClient(SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_ANON);
```

> ⚠️ Never commit `auth.js`. It is listed in `.gitignore` and must stay local.

### 3. Set up the Supabase database

Go to **Supabase Dashboard → SQL Editor → New Query**, paste the contents of `supabase_schema.sql` (available separately), and click **Run**.

This creates:
- `profiles` table — stores user name, email, sign-up time, last login
- `research_history` table — stores queries and full report markdown per user
- Row Level Security policies
- Auto-profile trigger on sign up
- Admin overview view

### 4. Run locally

Open `index.html` with [Live Server](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=ritwickdey.LiveServer) in VS Code, or simply open the file directly in your browser.

> The app runs at `http://127.0.0.1:5500` with Live Server.

---

## 🗄️ Database Schema

### `profiles`
| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | uuid | Links to Supabase `auth.users` |
| `full_name` | text | User's name from sign-up |
| `email` | text | User's email address |
| `created_at` | timestamptz | Account creation time |
| `last_sign_in` | timestamptz | Updated on every login |

### `research_history`
| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | uuid | Auto-generated primary key |
| `user_id` | uuid | Foreign key to `profiles.id` |
| `query` | text | The research question submitted |
| `report` | text | Full markdown report returned |
| `paper_count` | int | Number of papers cited |
| `total_seconds` | float | Pipeline execution time |
| `created_at` | timestamptz | When the search was run |

---

## 🔌 Backend API

The frontend communicates with the FastAPI backend via two endpoints:

### `POST /research`
Submit a new research query.

```json
// Request body
{
  "query": "Neuro-symbolic AI in medical diagnosis",
  "max_papers": 40,
  "papers_per_step": 10,
  "tool_timeout": 120.0
}

// Response
{
  "job_id": "7b8a2525-dca9-431b-86cf-3cdb615ade4f",
  "status": "pending",
  "message": "Job queued. Poll GET /research/{job_id} for updates."
}
```

### `GET /research/{job_id}`
Poll for job status. Call every 3 seconds until `status` is `"done"` or `"failed"`.

```json
// When done
{
  "job_id": "7b8a2525-...",
  "status": "done",
  "report": "## Introduction\n...",
  "paper_count": 23,
  "total_seconds": 76.0
}
```

**Status values:**
- `pending` — job queued, not started
- `running` — pipeline executing (~50–80s)
- `done` — report ready
- `failed` — error occurred, check `error` field

---

## 🔐 Authentication Flow

```
User clicks Sign Up
       │
       ▼
Supabase creates auth.users row
       │
       ▼
DB trigger auto-creates profiles row
       │
       ▼
Email confirmation sent (if enabled)
       │
       ▼
User clicks link → redirected to app.html
       │
       ▼
Session persists across page reloads
```

---

## 🌐 Deployment (Vercel)

1. Push your code to GitHub (ensure `auth.js` is not included)
2. Go to [vercel.com](https://vercel.com) → **New Project** → Import your GitHub repo
3. No build settings needed — it's a static site
4. After deploy, update two places with your new production URL:
   - **Supabase → Authentication → URL Configuration → Site URL**
   - **Supabase → Authentication → URL Configuration → Redirect URLs**
   - The `emailRedirectTo` value inside `app.js` signUp call

---

## ⚙️ Configuration Reference

| Variable | File | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `SUPABASE_URL` | `js/auth.js` | Your Supabase project URL |
| `SUPABASE_ANON` | `js/auth.js` | Your Supabase publishable key |
| `API_BASE` | `js/app.js` | Backend URL (Railway) |
| `STEP_DELAYS` | `js/app.js` | Timing for the 4 loading steps (seconds) |
| `MAX_POLLS` | `js/app.js` | Max polling attempts (default: 60 = 3 min) |
| `emailRedirectTo` | `js/app.js` | Post-verification redirect URL |

---

## 🛠️ Known Limitations

- **Free-tier rate limits** — The backend uses Groq and Gemini free tiers. Heavy usage will trigger `ResilientLLM: all providers exhausted`. Upgrading to paid API keys resolves this.
- **Job TTL** — Research jobs expire from Redis after 1 hour. Refreshing after that will show a 404 from the backend.
- **No offline support** — Requires active internet for both the backend pipeline and Supabase auth.

